Welcome to Devuan

Devuan GNU+Linux is a fork of Debian without systemd. 
Its Beta release marks an important milestone towards the sustainability 
and the continuation of Devuan as a universal base distribution.

https://devuan.org/

TAGS:
stable   : repo https://github.com/debitux/devuan-docker/tree/stable
testing  : repo https://github.com/debitux/devuan-docker/tree/testing
unstable : repo https://github.com/debitux/devuan-docker/tree/unstable
latest   : stable

Building:

DEPOT = stable testing unstable

debootstrap --keyring /root/.gnupg/pubring.gpg \
--arch amd64 $DEPOT rootfs http://packages.devuan.org/merged/

chroot rootfs
gpg --keyserver pgpkeys.mit.edu --recv-key  94532124541922FB
gpg -a --export 94532124541922FB | apt-key add -
exit

rm -rf rootfs/var/lib/apt/lists/* \
       rootfs/var/cache/apt/* \
       rootfs/var/cache/man/* \
       rootfs/usr/share/doc \
       rootfs/usr/share/doc-base \
       rootfs/usr/share/man \
       rootfs/usr/share/locale \ 
       rootfs/usr/share/zoneinfo

docker build -t debitux/devuan:$DEPOT .

Running :

docker run -i -t debitux/devuan:$DEPOT bash

